This is a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=4089

The script is based on the official css syntax file, you can find it  in here :http://fleiner.com/vim/syntax/css.vim

CSS3 syntax highlighting support. Include many of CSS3 Property,Attribute,Selector, support for the prefix " -moz-,-webkit- ,-o-,-ms- ", and complete the At-rule group, see : https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/CSS/At-rule . Added beautify CSS file function,  use the :CSSBeautify command.


For of the CSSBeautify command :

/* Original */

style

*{ width:680px ;
background-color:#FFF;
box-shadow: -1px 1px 3px #DDD;
padding: 10px
}
a:nth-of-type(2n) 
{
  background-color:#FFF!important
}
.class #id{border-radius:0px!important;}

/* After the command execution */

style

* {
width: 680px ;
background-color: #FFF ;
box-shadow: -1px 1px 3px #DDD ;
padding: 10px ;
}
a:nth-of-type(2n) {
background-color: #FFF !important;
}
.class #id {
border-radius: 0px !important;
}


